773	    /// function, \p funcDecl. This is used for adding the host-side function
774	    /// corresponding to the kernel. The code for this function will be
775	    /// automatically generated by the GenKernelExecution pass. \p funcTy is the
776	    /// type of \p funcDecl. \p devFuncName is the name of the device-side
777	    /// kernel. The placeholder definition lets any argument attributes be
